artment of the public security organ and the date specified should be issued for both accepted and rejected registration applications. Article 21: The fire department of the public security organ in provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities directly under the central government shall complete the preliminary review of first-level registered fire protection engineer qualification registration application materials and second-level registered fire protection engineer qualification registration approval work in accordance with the prescribed conditions and procedures within 20 working days from the date of accepting the registration application. The fire department should submit the first-level registered fire protection engineer qualification registration application materials and the preliminary review opinion to the Fire Department of the Ministry of Public Security for approval. The Fire Department of the Ministry of Public Security shall make a decision on whether to approve within 20 working days from the date of receiving the application materials and preliminary review opinions submitted by the provincial-level fire department of the public security organ. If a decision cannot be made within the prescribed time limit, the extended period and reasons should be notified to the applicant. The state implements a registration and practice management system for registered fire engineers. Those who obtain a first-class or second-class registered fire engineer qualification certificate can practice in the name of a corresponding level of registered fire engineer through registration authorities. The Fire Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security is the registration approval department for first-class registered fire engineer qualifications. The fire departments of public security organs in provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities directly under the central government are the registration approval departments for second-class registered fire engineer qualifications and are responsible for the preliminary examination of first-class registered fire engineer qualification registration. Those who obtain a first-class or second-class registered fire engineer qualification certificate and apply for registration should be employed by an approved fire technology service agency or fire safety key unit, and submit registration application materials to the fire department of the local public security organ (if the employing unit is an enterprise, submit it through the enterprise to the place where the business is registered). The fire department of the public security organ in provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities directly under the central government, upon receiving the registration application materials from the applicant, should inform the applicant of all the contents that need to be corrected on the spot or within five working days if the application materials are incomplete or do not conform to the legal form. If they fail to inform the applicant within the deadline, the materials will be deemed accepted from the date of receipt. Written certificates with the official seal of the fire department of the local public security organ and the date should be issued for accepted or rejected registration applications. Within 20 working days from the date of accepting the registration application, the fire department of the public security organ in provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities directly under the central government should complete the preliminary examination of first-class registered fire engineer qualification registration application materials and the registration approval work of second-class registered fire engineer qualifications according to the prescribed conditions and procedures, and submit the application materials for first-class registered fire engineer qualification registration and the preliminary examination opinions to the Fire Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security for approval. The Fire Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security shall make a decision on whether to approve within 20 working days from the date of receiving the application materials and the preliminary examination opinions submitted by the provincial public security organ fire department. If a decision cannot be made within the prescribed time limit, the applicant should be informed of the extended deadline and reasons. The registration approval department shall issue and deliver the corresponding level of registration certificate within 10 working days from the date of making the approval decision. The validity period of each registration certificate is three years. The registration certificate is the practice certificate of the corresponding level of registered fire engineer during its validity period and is kept and used by the registered fire engineer. For initial registration, the application must be submitted within one year from the date of obtaining a first-class or second-class registered fire engineer qualification certificate. If the initial registration is overdue, it must meet the requirements of continuing education specified in these regulations. Specific methods for initial registration, renewal registration, change of registration, cancellation of registration, and rejection of registration shall be separately stipulated by the Ministry of Public Security. Continuing education is a necessary condition for renewal registration, re-registration, and overdue initial registration of registered fire engineers. During each registration period, registered fire engineers of various levels should complete the corresponding continuing education according to regulations. The registration approval department shall promptly announce the registration-related information of registered fire engineers to the society, establish an integrity file for registered fire engineers, and implement credit management for their practice activities. Article 27: Registration management d